the [last]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Bd in xcvi. 18:) but the Arabs hardly, or in nowise, know this [attribution of a sing. to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zabaAniyapN","text_ar":"زَبَانِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], holding it to be a pl. having no sing., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAbiylu","text_ar":"اَبَابِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaAdiydu","text_ar":"عَبَادِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Akh, S.) With the Arabs [of the classical age] it signifies The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uraT","text_ar":"شُرَط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. in the earlier sense of the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"braves of an army,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or in the later sense of the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"armed attendants, officers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soldiers, of the prefect of the police"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) this is the primary signification: (Bd in xcvi. 18:) the sing. being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uroTiY~N","text_ar":"شُرْطِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and also signifying the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutamar~id","text_ar":"مُتَمَرِّد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who exalts himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is insolent and audacious, in pride and in acts of rebellion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disobedience,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] of the jinn, or genii, and of mankind: (K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adiydN","text_ar":"شَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (Secr, K:) each of these two significations [and the first also] being from the meaning of “ pushing, ” or “ thrusting. ” (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~abaAniyapu","text_ar":"الزَّبَانِيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain angels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tormentors of the damned in Hell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] so called because of their thrusting the people of the fire thereto; (Katádeh, S, Msb; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the angels"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned in the Kur [lxvi. 6] as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gilaAZN $idaAdN","text_ar":"غِلَاظٌ شِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Zj,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rough"},{"kind":"text","text":"in speech or in disposition,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong"},{"kind":"text","text":"in deeds or in make. (Bd.)"}],"source_refs":["Akh","Zj","S","K","TA","Ks","Secr"]}]}}